Package com.intellij.refactoring

Interface MoveDestination

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AutocreatingMoveDestination, AutocreatingSingleSourceRootMoveDestination, MultipleRootsMoveDestination, SingleSourceRootMoveDestination

    public interface MoveDestination
    Represents a destination of Move Classes/Packages refactoring. Destination of Move refactoring is generally a single package, and various MoveDestinations control how moved items will be layouted in directories corresponding to target packages. Instances of this interface can be obtained via methods of RefactoringFactory.
    See Also:
    JavaRefactoringFactory.createSourceFolderPreservingMoveDestination(String), JavaRefactoringFactory.createSourceRootMoveDestination(java.lang.String, com.intellij.openapi.vfs.VirtualFile)
